Adventurer Emoni: Please don't worry about me, madam... I
am the proud daughter of a noble... I cannot accept
charity.

Adventurer Emoni: Or is it a lowly request? Please ask a
prostitute for something like that.

Hmm... You seem to be an adventurer. Would you mind helping
me with my work?

Adventurer Emoni: ...I cannot accept requests from someone
whose name I don't know.

Great Widow: I have discarded my name, it's embarrassing,
but everyone calls me the Great Widow.
Great Widow: Nice to meet you... um...

Adventurer Emoni: I am Emoni, madam. I cannot accept being
called great by someone I don't acknowledge.

The encounter with the Great Widow will change Emoni's life.
The courage to silence even nobles, the negotiation skills
that make even merchants tremble. Those abilities were what
Emoni admired and desired.

What shook Emoni's heart more than anything was the fact
that she was a woman. Being able to fight on equal terms
with men, and even surpass them. The Great Widow was the
embodiment of Emoni's ideal.

Guided by the Great Widow, Emoni joined the Adventurer's
Guild. Agonia and Shimos showed reluctance, but ultimately
her membership was approved.

During this time, Emoni was far from being reckless or
arrogant. She had a strong desire not to bring shame to the
Great Widow who had recommended her. Emoni was working not
for herself, but for the sake of others for the first time.

It was a refreshing and fulfilling experience. For the sake
of the clients, for the sake of her comrades, and above all,
for the Great Widow. Emoni carried out numerous tasks such
as investigations, escorts, and negotiations.

Agonia was uneasy about Emoni being recognized within the
guild. The reason was that Emoni's driving force was the
Great Widow. Emoni didn't even consider what kind of person
she was.

Emoni believed that her feelings towards the Great Widow
were a mixture of admiration and dependence. She wondered
what would happen to her when the Great Widow passed away.
Agonia gradually began to grow wary of Emoni.
